latestPosts.caption:
Genetically, I do have good hair – but trust me, maintenance still matters! Even with good genes, bad habits can ruin hair quality over time.

1)Using satin pillow covers – I don’t wake up with frizzy hair or breakage! This tiny change has made my hair smoother 

2)Washing every 2–3 days – I don’t overwash anymore. It keeps the natural oils balanced and my scalp healthier.

3)Eating almonds & walnuts – These are rich in biotin, omega-3s, and vitamin E – all great for hair strength and shine.

4)Minimal heat styling – I avoid heating tools unless necessary.

💇🏻‍♀️Style tip if you have long, straight hair like mine:
Go for long layers with slightly long curtain bangs. It adds shape and volume without sacrificing length, and the bangs slims down the face and frames it well.
